<p>Here in Phoenix during the summer, I avoid turning on my oven whenever possible. That’s when no-bake recipes become my go-to.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1000" height="1500" data-pin-description="This peanut butter chocolate no bake cheesecake has a buttery graham cracker crust, ultra creamy filling, and rich chocolate ganache topping. Easy, smooth, and perfect for summer, when you don't want to turn your oven on. Simple and delicious summer recipe perfect for entertaining." data-pin-title="My Favorite No-Bake Cheesecake Recipe" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201000%201500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="overhead view of cheesecake cut into slices with a cake server about to remove one " class="wp-image-92889" data-lazy-srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/easy-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake.jpg 1000w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/easy-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake-250x375.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/easy-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake-768x1152.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-lazy-src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/easy-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake.jpg"><noscript><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1000" height="1500" data-pin-description="This peanut butter chocolate no bake cheesecake has a buttery graham cracker crust, ultra creamy filling, and rich chocolate ganache topping. Easy, smooth, and perfect for summer, when you don't want to turn your oven on. Simple and delicious summer recipe perfect for entertaining." data-pin-title="My Favorite No-Bake Cheesecake Recipe" src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/easy-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake.jpg" alt="overhead view of cheesecake cut into slices with a cake server about to remove one " class="wp-image-92889" srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/easy-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake.jpg 1000w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/easy-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake-250x375.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/easy-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake-768x1152.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"></noscript></figure>



<p>Traditional cheesecakes take over an hour to bake, often involving the nuisance of a water bath, and then take hours longer to cool and chill. This recipe skips most of those steps, saving so much time <em>and</em> keeping your kitchen cool!</p>



<p>Bonus: the peanut butter flavor actually shines more in a no-bake cheesecake. It’s not diluted by a bunch of eggs or the process of baking. So the flavor stays bold, nutty, and nostalgic.</p>



<p>If you love chocolate and peanut butter like I do, this peanut butter cheesecake recipe is hard to beat!</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="998" height="1500" data-pin-description="If you love chocolate and peanut butter like I do, this peanut butter cheesecake recipe is hard to beat! Traditional cheesecakes take over an hour to bake, often involving the nuisance of a water bath, and then take hours longer to cool and chill. This recipe skips most of those steps, saving so much time and keeping your kitchen cool! Bonus: the peanut butter flavor actually shines more in a no-bake cheesecake. It's not diluted by a bunch of eggs or the process of baking. So the flavor stays bold, nutty, and nostalgic." data-pin-title="No Bake Cheesecake (Like a Giant Reese's Cup!)" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20998%201500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="slices of cheesecake on small dessert plates on a marble surface" class="wp-image-92895" data-lazy-srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/no-bake-homemade-peanut-butter-cheesecake.jpg 998w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/no-bake-homemade-peanut-butter-cheesecake-250x376.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/no-bake-homemade-peanut-butter-cheesecake-768x1154.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 998px) 100vw, 998px" data-lazy-src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/no-bake-homemade-peanut-butter-cheesecake.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="998" height="1500" data-pin-description="If you love chocolate and peanut butter like I do, this peanut butter cheesecake recipe is hard to beat! Traditional cheesecakes take over an hour to bake, often involving the nuisance of a water bath, and then take hours longer to cool and chill. This recipe skips most of those steps, saving so much time and keeping your kitchen cool! Bonus: the peanut butter flavor actually shines more in a no-bake cheesecake. It's not diluted by a bunch of eggs or the process of baking. So the flavor stays bold, nutty, and nostalgic." data-pin-title="No Bake Cheesecake (Like a Giant Reese's Cup!)" src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/no-bake-homemade-peanut-butter-cheesecake.jpg" alt="slices of cheesecake on small dessert plates on a marble surface" class="wp-image-92895" srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/no-bake-homemade-peanut-butter-cheesecake.jpg 998w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/no-bake-homemade-peanut-butter-cheesecake-250x376.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/no-bake-homemade-peanut-butter-cheesecake-768x1154.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 998px) 100vw, 998px"></noscript></figure>


