4 13.2265 9.34891 13.5179C9.14037 13.2238 8.86431 12.9841 8.54392 12.8188C8.22352 12.6535 7.86815 12.5675 7.50763 12.568C7.14711 12.5685 6.79198 12.6555 6.47205 12.8217C6.15213 12.9879 5.87675 13.2285 5.66904 13.5231C5.52788 13.2941 5.3422 13.0957 5.123 12.9398C4.90379 12.7838 4.65552 12.6734 4.39289 12.6151C4.13025 12.5568 3.85859 12.5518 3.59397 12.6003C3.32936 12.6489 3.07719 12.7501 2.85238 12.8978C2.68782 12.5633 2.60185 12.1956 2.60104 11.8227C2.62492 11.271 2.86623 10.7512 3.27222 10.3769C3.67822 10.0025 4.21588 9.80416 4.76771 9.82506Z"></path></g><defs><clippath id="clip0_341_958"><rect width="26" height="26"></rect></clippath></defs></svg></span><span class="kb-adv-text-inner">Recipe Ingredients</span></h2>


<p>The below ingredients and how they’re purchased and prepared make the difference between a no-bake cheesecake that slices beautifully and one that turns into a soft, underset mess.</p>



<p><strong>Graham Crackers: </strong>Use your food processor to finely grind the crackers for a crust that holds together. You can also use store-bought crumbs. If they are too coarse, the crust will crumble.</p>



<p><strong></strong><em>Substitutions: </em>You can substitute the same amount of fine crumbs (about 1 cup, or 227 grams) from digestive biscuits, vanilla wafers, or chocolate graham crackers.</p>



<p><strong>Cream Cheese: </strong>It’s essential to only use full-fat brick cream cheese, not cream cheese from a tub. I strongly recommend the Philadelphia brand. Many generic brands are too watery for no-bake cheesecake. Make sure it’s fully softened to room temperature before using, otherwise your cheesecake will be lumpy.</p>



<p><strong>Powdered Sugar: </strong>This is used in place of granulated sugar because it dissolves more readily into the no-bake filling for a smooth texture. </p>



<p><strong>Peanut Butter: </strong>Use whatever you enjoy eating. My preferred choice is the Kirkland Signature Organic Peanut Butter, so long as it’s been very well stirred. Natural peanut butter that only contains peanuts + nuts will offer a bolder flavor, but seriously, it must be very well stirred (no dry bits, no oily bits). Conventional peanut butter will work too, but your filling may be sweeter.</p>



<p><strong>Heavy Cream </strong>(36% milkfat)<strong>: </strong>Just half a cup helps create a silky, smooth, and rich texture while still allowing the filling to firm up in the fridge. Without this, the filling is overly dense and heavy. Don’t substitute this.</p>



<p><strong>Chocolate: </strong>For the ganache, I prefer semisweet chocolate to balance the sweetness and complement the nuttiness of the peanut butter filling. I find bittersweet chocolate to be too dark for this recipe. You can try using milk chocolate, but note the ganache will be softer.</p>
</div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id30489_265f1e-7b alignnone how-to wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column30489_f12501-1c"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<h2 class="kt-adv-heading30489_2be3be-e2 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading" data-kb-block="kb-adv-heading30489_2be3be-e2" id="toc-how-to-make-no-bake-peanut-butter-cheesecake-step-by-step">How to Make No Bake Peanut Butter Cheesecake (Step by Step)</h2>


<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id30489_109315-22 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column30489_c1d898-7f"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-kadence-image kb-image30489_f8ca1f-e5 size-full kb-image-is-ratio-size"><div class="kb-is-ratio-image kb-image-ratio-square"><img decoding="async" width="998" height="1500" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20998%201500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" class="kb-img wp-image-92893" data-lazy-srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/00-graham-cracker-crust.jpg 998w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/00-graham-cracker-crust-250x376.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/00-graham-cracker-crust-768x1154.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 998px) 100vw, 998px" data-lazy-src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/00-graham-cracker-crust.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="998" height="1500" src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/00-graham-cracker-crust.jpg" alt="" class="kb-img wp-image-92893" srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/00-graham-cracker-crust.jpg 998w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/00-graham-cracker-crust-250x376.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/00-graham-cracker-crust-768x1154.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 998px) 100vw, 998px"></noscript></div></figure>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-infobox kt-info-box30489_a43438-94"><span class="kt-blocks-info-box-link-wrap info-box-link kt-blocks-info-box-media-align-left kt-info-halign-left kb-info-box-vertical-media-align-top"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media kt-info-media-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-number-container kt-info-number-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-number-inner-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-number">1</div></div></div></div></div><div class="kt-infobox-textcontent"><p class="kt-blocks-info-box-text"><strong>Prepare graham cracker crust</strong>. Pulse graham crackers in a food processor until very fine (or use store-bought crumbs—don’t crush by hand, they won’t be fine enough for the crust to hold without baking).</p></div></span></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column30489_84a58a-41"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-kadence-image kb-image30489_910709-d4 size-full kb-image-is-ratio-size"><div class="kb-is-ratio-image kb-image-ratio-square"><img decoding="async" width="1000" height="1500" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201000%201500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="graham cracker crust pressed into a springform pan on a marble surface" class="kb-img wp-image-92885" data-lazy-srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/01-prepare-graham-cracker-crust.jpg 1000w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/01-prepare-graham-cracker-crust-250x375.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/01-prepare-graham-cracker-crust-768x1152.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-lazy-src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/01-prepare-graham-cracker-crust.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1000" height="1500" src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/01-prepare-graham-cracker-crust.jpg" alt="graham cracker crust pressed into a springform pan on a marble surface" class="kb-img wp-image-92885" srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/01-prepare-graham-cracker-crust.jpg 1000w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/01-prepare-graham-cracker-crust-250x375.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/01-prepare-graham-cracker-crust-768x1152.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"></noscript></div></figure>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-infobox kt-info-box30489_ad4f40-78"><span class="kt-blocks-info-box-link-wrap info-box-link kt-blocks-info-box-media-align-left kt-info-halign-left kb-info-box-vertical-media-align-top"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media kt-info-media-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-number-container kt-info-number-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-number-inner-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-number">2</div></div></div></div></div><div class="kt-infobox-textcontent"><p class="kt-blocks-info-box-text"><strong>Press crust into pan</strong>. Press firmly into a greased 9-inch springform pan using the bottom of a glass or measuring cup.</p></div></span></div>
</div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id30489_8a63b5-9d alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-2-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column30489_027ca4-ca"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-kadence-image kb-image30489_8935b9-d5 size-full kb-image-is-ratio-size"><div class="kb-is-ratio-image kb-image-ratio-square"><img decoding="async" width="1000" height="1500" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201000%201500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="adding peanut butter filling to the graham cracker crust" class="kb-img wp-image-92886" data-lazy-srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/02-no-bake-cheesecake-filling.jpg 1000w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/02-no-bake-cheesecake-filling-250x375.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/02-no-bake-cheesecake-filling-768x1152.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-lazy-src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/02-no-bake-cheesecake-filling.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1000" height="1500" src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/02-no-bake-cheesecake-filling.jpg" alt="adding peanut butter filling to the graham cracker crust" class="kb-img wp-image-92886" srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/02-no-bake-cheesecake-filling.jpg 1000w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/02-no-bake-cheesecake-filling-250x375.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/02-no-bake-cheesecake-filling-768x1152.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"></noscript></div></figure>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-infobox kt-info-box30489_8c7d84-fd"><span class="kt-blocks-info-box-link-wrap info-box-link kt-blocks-info-box-media-align-left kt-info-halign-left kb-info-box-vertical-media-align-top"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media kt-info-media-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-number-container kt-info-number-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-number-inner-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-number">3</div></div></div></div></div><div class="kt-infobox-textcontent"><p class="kt-blocks-info-box-text"><strong>Fill the pan</strong>. Pour filling into assembled crust, smoothing with a spatula. Refrigerate for at least 6 hours, but overnight is best.</p></div></span></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column30489_1b28cc-be"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<figure class="wp-block-kadence-image kb-image30489_32d903-78 size-full kb-image-is-ratio-size"><div class="kb-is-ratio-image kb-image-ratio-square"><img decoding="async" width="998" height="1500" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20998%201500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="topping chilled cheesecake with ganache" class="kb-img wp-image-92887" data-lazy-srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/03-ganache-topping-for-no-bake-cheesecake.jpg 998w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/03-ganache-topping-for-no-bake-cheesecake-250x376.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/03-ganache-topping-for-no-bake-cheesecake-768x1154.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 998px) 100vw, 998px" data-lazy-src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/03-ganache-topping-for-no-bake-cheesecake.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="998" height="1500" src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/03-ganache-topping-for-no-bake-cheesecake.jpg" alt="topping chilled cheesecake with ganache" class="kb-img wp-image-92887" srcset="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/03-ganache-topping-for-no-bake-cheesecake.jpg 998w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/03-ganache-topping-for-no-bake-cheesecake-250x376.jpg 250w, https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/03-ganache-topping-for-no-bake-cheesecake-768x1154.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 998px) 100vw, 998px"></noscript></div></figure>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-infobox kt-info-box30489_41e5f2-e2"><span class="kt-blocks-info-box-link-wrap info-box-link kt-blocks-info-box-media-align-left kt-info-halign-left kb-info-box-vertical-media-align-top"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-media kt-info-media-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-number-container kt-info-number-animate-none"><div class="kadence-info-box-number-inner-container"><div class="kt-blocks-info-box-number">4</div></div></div></div></div><div class="kt-infobox-textcontent"><p class="kt-blocks-info-box-text"><strong>Add ganache topping</strong>. Pour over the chilled cheesecake and spread with an icing spatula.</p></div></span></div>
</div></div>

</div></div></div></div>

</div></div>

<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id30489_587c9b-85 alignnone bordered-box wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

