 20.7716L20.5553 15.949C20.6361 15.6815 20.9178 15.531 21.1821 15.6121C21.4464 15.6931 21.5969 15.9774 21.5165 16.2437L20.0605 21.0662C19.9801 21.3326 19.6992 21.4846 19.4337 21.4032Z"></path><path d="M10.965 18.8075C10.6994 18.7261 10.5502 18.4422 10.6306 18.1758L12.0865 13.3533C12.1673 13.0858 12.449 12.9353 12.7134 13.0164C12.9777 13.0974 13.1281 13.3817 13.0477 13.648L11.5918 18.4705C11.5113 18.7369 11.2305 18.8889 10.965 18.8075Z"></path><path d="M17.2169 22.7511L12.0626 21.1708C11.7971 21.0894 11.6478 20.8055 11.7282 20.5391C11.8087 20.2728 12.0907 20.1211 12.3551 20.2022L17.5094 21.7825C17.7749 21.8639 17.9242 22.1478 17.8437 22.4141C17.7633 22.6805 17.4825 22.8325 17.2169 22.7511Z"></path></g><defs><clippath id="clip0_341_1051"><rect width="30.1602" height="30.354" transform="matrix(0.956072 0.293133 0.289023 -0.957322 0 29.0586)"></rect></clippath></defs></svg></span><span class="kb-adv-text-inner">Tessa’s Tips</span></h2>


<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Grind graham crackers very finely for a crust that holds together.</li>



<li>Press the crust firmly using a measuring cup to compact the crumbs.</li>



<li>Use brick-style cream cheese only. Spreadable cream cheese prevents proper setting.</li>



<li>Make sure cream cheese is fully softened before mixing.</li>



<li>Chill the cheesecake at least 6 hours, but overnight is best.</li>



<li>If slices feel too soft, freeze the cheesecake 30 minutes before cutting.</li>



<li>Use a hot knife for clean slices. Run under hot water and wipe dry between cuts.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

</div></div>


